1 AN ACT concerning housing; providing that court records in eviction
2 actions where the underlying rental agreement is governed by the
3 residential landlord and tenant act shall be sealed for certain periods;
4 requiring expungement of certain court records of such eviction
5 actions; providing that certain violations of this act constitute
6 unconscionable acts or practices under the provisions of the Kansas
7 consumer protection act; requiring mediation in eviction actions where
8 the underlying rental agreement is governed by the residential landlord
9 and tenant act unless the court finds that mediation would not aid the
10 parties materially; amending K.S.A. 61-3804 and 61-3806 and K.S.A.
11 2024 Supp. 60-2617 and 61-3807 and repealing the existing sections.
12
13 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
14 New Section 1. (a) Upon the filing of a petition for eviction pursuant
15 to K.S.A. 61-3801 et seq., and amendments thereto, where the underlying
16 rental agreement is governed by K.S.A. 58-2540 et seq., and amendments
17 thereto, the court shall automatically seal the court file, including the
18 petition commencing the action and any other pleadings, proof of service,
19 any findings and orders of the court and all other papers, records,
20 proceedings and evidence, including exhibits and transcripts of the
21 testimony. Such filings and the allegations in the filings shall be
22 confidential and shall not be disclosed to any person except as provided by
23 this section. Upon the sealing of the court file, the case records and any
24 information concerning the case shall not be made available or transferred
25 to any third party and shall only be available to the following persons:
26 (1) The tenant whose court file is sealed and any party or attorney
27 who has made an appearance in the case;
28 (2) the court; and
29 (3) the clerk of the court responsible for maintaining records.
30 (b) (1) Except as provided in paragraph (2), the court shall not unseal
31 a case that is sealed pursuant to this section if the case:
32 (A) Does not result in a judgment;
33 (B) is dismissed, including, but not limited to, dismissal pursuant to a
34 mediation agreement or agreement between the plaintiff and defendant; or
35 (C) results in a judgment entered in favor of the defendant.

