1 (2) The court may unseal a case that is sealed pursuant to this section
2 if the defendant requests unsealing or the plaintiff and defendant agree to
3 unsealing.
4 (c) (1) Except as provided in paragraph (2), the court shall unseal a
5 case that is sealed pursuant to this section if a default judgment or
6 judgment is entered in favor of the plaintiff.
7 (2) The court shall not unseal a case described in paragraph (1) if:
8 (A) The plaintiff and defendant agree to keep the case sealed;
9 (B) the court finds good cause or that it is in the best interest of
10 justice to keep the case sealed. Good cause includes, but is not limited to:
11 (i) A tenant who is a victim of domestic violence;
12 (ii) fault by both the plaintiff and defendant; or
13 (iii) any other identified safety, property or privacy interest.
14 (d) (1) A consumer reporting agency, tenant screening agency,
15 property management company, landlord or those standing in the position
16 of property management shall not collect or disseminate, cause to be
17 disseminated or permit the dissemination of any eviction filing or eviction
18 case information that is subject to automatic sealing by the court pursuant
19 to this section.
20 (2) Any violation of this subsection shall be deemed to be a deceptive
21 or unconscionable act or practice under the provisions of the Kansas
22 consumer protection act and shall be subject to the remedies and
23 enforcement provisions of the Kansas consumer protection act. Any person
24 alleging a violation of this subsection may bring a private action to seek
25 relief pursuant to K.S.A. 50-634 or 50-636, and amendments thereto, and
26 such person shall be considered a consumer pursuant to K.S.A. 50-624,
27 and amendments thereto, for the purposes of such private action. The
28 requirements and remedies of this subsection are in addition to and not in
29 substitution for any other requirements and remedies provided by law.
30 (e) (1) Except as otherwise provided in this subsection, an unsealed
31 or public record of default judgment or judgment in an eviction action
32 where the underlying rental agreement is governed by K.S.A. 58-2540 et
33 seq., and amendments thereto, shall be automatically expunged if the
34 judgment, including a monetary award, if any, is satisfied and two years
35 have passed from the date of judgment.
36 (2) If a tenant has an additional judgment entered in an eviction
37 action where the underlying rental agreement is governed by K.S.A. 58-
38 2540 et seq., and amendments thereto, within the two-year period
39 described in paragraph (1), the preceding judgment shall not be expunged
40 until the ensuing judgment is eligible for automatic expungement at two
41 years after the most recent judgment.
42 (3) In accordance with federal law and requirements, a public housing
43 authority may request access to eviction judgment history for the past

