10 3804. (a) The petition shall describe the premises for which possession is
11 sought and why the plaintiff is seeking possession. If there is rent due for
12 possession of the premises, the petition may include a request for
13 judgment for that amount or the plaintiff may bring a subsequent lawsuit
14 for that amount.
15 (b) In an action where the underlying rental agreement is governed
16 by K.S.A. 58-2540 et seq., and amendments thereto, the petition, court
17 records and file shall be sealed as provided by section 1, and amendments
