19 Sec. 4. K.S.A. 61-3806 is hereby amended to read as follows: 61-
20 3806. (a) Except as provided in subsection (c), a defendant shall either
21 appear in person or by counsel at the time and date set forth in the
22 summons or file on or before such date a written answer.
23 (b) The answer, when filed, shall contain the information as required
24 under subsection (b) of K.S.A. 61-2904(b), and amendments thereto.
25 (c) In an action where the underlying rental agreement is governed
26 by K.S.A. 58-2540 et seq., and amendments thereto, the court shall:
27 (1) Allow the defendant to appear by two-way electronic audio-video
28 communication between the defendant and the judge in lieu of personal
29 presence of the defendant; and
30 (2) order mediation unless the court finds that mediation would not
31 aid the parties materially.
32 Sec. 5. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 61-3807 is hereby amended to read as
33 follows: 61-3807. (a) If a trial is necessary, the trial shall be conducted
34 within 14 days after the appearance date stated in the summons.
35 (b) (1) Except as provided in paragraph (2), no continuance shall be
36 granted unless the defendant requesting a continuance shall file a bond
37 with good and sufficient security approved by the court, conditioned for
38 the payment of all damages and rent that may accrue if judgment is entered
39 against the defendant.
40 (2) In an action where the underlying rental agreement is governed
41 by K.S.A. 58-2540 et seq., and amendments thereto, the court shall order a
42 continuance if the parties are participating in mediation.
